WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:03.635
Dre:<i> Americans are consumers.</i>

00:03.637 --> 00:06.505
<i>We want the best,
the baddest, and the biggest...</i>

00:06.507 --> 00:09.174
♪ I'm telling you, oh, it all falls down ♪
<i>Unless, of course, the baddest is the smallest.</i>

00:09.176 --> 00:12.478
<i>Then you want that, until
the baddest gets bigger again.</i>

00:12.480 --> 00:14.446
<i>We're all consumers,</i>

00:14.448 --> 00:16.181
<i>but at the risk
of stereotyping us...</i>

00:16.183 --> 00:18.984
♪ I'm telling you, oh ♪ <i>...Black
folks really get it in.</i>

00:18.986 --> 00:21.286
<i>We just do.
But think about it...</i>

00:21.288 --> 00:23.555
♪ I'm telling you, oh ♪ <i>if you didn't
get a paycheck for 400 years...</i>

00:23.557 --> 00:25.124
♪ It all falls down ♪ <i>...When
you did finally get one,</i>

00:25.126 --> 00:26.625
<i>you might want to spend it.</i>

00:26.627 --> 00:27.993
♪ I'm telling you, oh ♪
<i>of course, nowadays,</i>

00:27.995 --> 00:31.063
<i>that kind of attitude
can get you in trouble.</i>

00:31.065 --> 00:33.298
♪ I'm telling you, oh ♪
<i>that's the thing about money.</i>

00:33.300 --> 00:35.334
<i>Everybody wants to have it,</i>

00:35.336 --> 00:37.703
<i>but nobody wants
to talk about it...</i>

00:37.705 --> 00:39.471
♪ I'm telling you, oh ♪
<i>Which can lead to problems.</i>

00:39.473 --> 00:41.006
♪ It all falls down ♪
[ Gasps ] We owe what?!

00:41.008 --> 00:43.809
Let me see that.

00:45.413 --> 00:47.146
Mm, hold on.

00:47.148 --> 00:49.214
Wha...

00:51.052 --> 00:52.751
Holy slick Rick!

00:58.259 --> 01:00.826
How did we spend this much
on our credit cards?

01:00.828 --> 01:02.761
It was a big month, bow.

01:02.763 --> 01:05.497
We took the kids to Disneyland,
we replaced the water heater,

01:05.499 --> 01:08.901
oh, and I got
these fly new reading glasses.

01:08.903 --> 01:11.904
Dre, come on, now we have
the kids' tuition coming up.

01:11.906 --> 01:13.439
And isn't this
the property-tax bill?

01:13.441 --> 01:14.440
Don't worry about that.

01:14.442 --> 01:17.609
I have an 819 fico score.

01:17.611 --> 01:19.278
I think we're gonna be okay.

01:19.280 --> 01:20.846
I don't understand
where all the money goes.

01:20.848 --> 01:22.281
[ Sighs ]
Me neither.

01:22.283 --> 01:24.783
Look what I had overnighted
from Japan.

01:24.785 --> 01:27.119
That is ostrich.

01:27.121 --> 01:28.921
First of all,
those are beautiful.

01:28.923 --> 01:30.556
Thank you.

01:30.558 --> 01:31.790
Secondly, do you ever wonder
if we're living too large?

01:31.792 --> 01:33.225
[ Dramatic chord plays ]

01:33.227 --> 01:34.026
We're broke.

01:34.028 --> 01:35.627
Wait, what?

01:35.629 --> 01:37.062
We just heard mom say
we're living too large.

01:37.064 --> 01:38.931
I knew this was too much house.

01:38.933 --> 01:40.032
What are we gonna do?

01:40.034 --> 01:41.533
I'm two years away from college,

01:41.535 --> 01:45.370
so this is more of a "you"
problem than a "we" problem.

01:45.372 --> 01:47.239
Well, I've got a "disaster
preparedness" folder.

01:47.241 --> 01:48.574
Of course you do.

01:48.576 --> 01:51.610
Let's see, "earthquakes,"
"super volcano," "peak oil."

01:51.612 --> 01:52.644
[ Gasps ] Ooh!

01:52.646 --> 01:54.746
<i>Congratulations, junior.</i>

01:54.748 --> 01:57.449
<i>If you're watching this, you've
survived the zombie apocalypse.</i>

01:57.451 --> 02:00.652
Oh. Sorry. Wrong video.

02:00.654 --> 02:01.887
Dude.

02:01.889 --> 02:04.556
Oh, here it is.
"Financial ruin."

02:04.558 --> 02:07.392
I'm supposed to start
day-trading... I think.

02:07.394 --> 02:09.995
For some reason,
I wrote this plan in dothraki.

02:09.997 --> 02:12.131
<i>Anha dothrak chek asshekh.</i>

02:12.133 --> 02:13.799
Can we live with you
in the dorm?

02:13.801 --> 02:15.734
Just you two, right?

02:15.736 --> 02:17.736
[ Continues speaking Dothraki ]

02:17.738 --> 02:20.439
We earn a good living, bow.

02:20.441 --> 02:22.007
We're doing fine, okay?

02:22.009 --> 02:23.142
And this...
This property-tax thing...

02:23.144 --> 02:24.143
Don't even worry about that.

02:24.145 --> 02:26.845
My guy, James brown,
is all over it.

02:26.847 --> 02:29.948
I still can't believe our
accountant is named James brown.

02:29.950 --> 02:32.518
He is the hardest-working man
in accounting.

02:32.520 --> 02:34.419
And please,

02:34.421 --> 02:38.690
do not project your weird
relationship with money onto me.

02:38.692 --> 02:39.992
What weird relationship?

02:39.994 --> 02:41.860
Mommy, what's this?

02:41.862 --> 02:43.262
That's money.

02:43.264 --> 02:45.130
It's an artificial
masculine construct

02:45.132 --> 02:47.332
that fosters hostility and war

02:47.334 --> 02:50.002
and builds a wall
between you and love.

02:50.004 --> 02:52.871
Now, eat your mung beans.

02:52.873 --> 02:54.940
Are you sweating?

02:54.942 --> 02:56.041
Yes, Dre, I'm sweating

02:56.043 --> 02:57.709
because I don't like talking
about money.

02:57.711 --> 03:00.145
We made a deal...
You would be the money guy,

03:00.147 --> 03:01.813
and I was gonna be
the kid wrangler.

03:01.815 --> 03:03.348
Yeah. Do you want to
be the kid wrangler?

03:03.350 --> 03:05.017
No. 'Cause there's an e-blast
that needs to go out

03:05.019 --> 03:06.118
about wheat allergies. No, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no, no!

03:06.120 --> 03:07.786
And we still haven't
figured out summer camp.

03:07.788 --> 03:09.354
Unh-unh! Unh-unh!

03:09.356 --> 03:11.356
And the twins' class
is looking for a parent

03:11.358 --> 03:12.891
to go on a field trip
to the solid-waste plant.

03:12.893 --> 03:15.827
Enough! Enough, already!
Okay, bow?

03:15.829 --> 03:19.131
Damn it, bow, I'm all over
this money thing, okay? Okay.

03:19.133 --> 03:22.334
I know every cent coming in
and every cent going out.

03:22.336 --> 03:24.036
Mm-hmm. Hey, son, uh,
I need to hold a "g."

03:24.038 --> 03:25.504
I got a tip on a pony,

03:25.506 --> 03:27.172
and I'm a little light
on walking-around money.

03:27.174 --> 03:28.240
Oh, sure.
No problem, pops.

03:28.242 --> 03:29.074
Just a grand?
Just a grand.

03:29.076 --> 03:30.209
"Just a grand."

03:30.211 --> 03:31.543
There you go, right there.
My man.

03:31.545 --> 03:33.946
Okay, you got it.

03:35.516 --> 03:38.317
Okay, um...

03:38.319 --> 03:43.021
Let's just, uh, put that,
uh, under, uh, "going out."

03:43.023 --> 03:45.557
So, you really think day-trading
is going to work?

03:45.559 --> 03:47.192
Because your zombie plan
was a mess.

03:47.194 --> 03:49.595
You thought after the apocalypse
you'd still have Internet.

03:49.597 --> 03:50.696
Or your eyeballs.

03:50.698 --> 03:51.997
What you kids doing?

03:51.999 --> 03:53.599
I'm gonna start day-trading.

03:53.601 --> 03:55.734
Day-trading?
That ain't nothing but gambling.

03:55.736 --> 03:57.102
Proud of you, boy.

03:57.104 --> 03:58.036
Just make sure you know
what you're doing.

03:58.038 --> 03:59.338
He doesn't.

03:59.340 --> 04:00.739
Just do like I do
at the track...

04:00.741 --> 04:03.742
Find an inside edge.

04:03.744 --> 04:06.678
My insider at the track
is a hot-dog guy named Luis.

04:06.680 --> 04:09.348
He knows the deal on every race,
every horse, every jockey,

04:09.350 --> 04:11.583
who's up, who's down, who's out.
He's the best.

04:11.585 --> 04:14.119
Well, if he knows so much,
why is he still the hot-dog guy?

04:16.890 --> 04:18.330
You make a strong point,
little girl.

04:19.059 --> 04:20.859
I need to call James brown.

04:20.861 --> 04:22.527
And then my grandma
looked up at me...

04:22.529 --> 04:23.729
[ Snores ]

04:23.731 --> 04:24.896
And with her last breath,

04:24.898 --> 04:26.265
she said something
I will never forget...

04:26.267 --> 04:27.866
Stevens: Lunch!

04:27.868 --> 04:29.234
Oh, thank god. That was close.
Yes.

04:29.236 --> 04:30.535
Now, whose turn is it to pay?

04:30.537 --> 04:32.304
I got it.
Don't worry about it. I got it.

04:32.306 --> 04:34.406
Let me see something.

04:34.408 --> 04:37.242
My god, what are you,
a high-end prostitute?

04:37.244 --> 04:39.211
Yeah. What are you doing walking
around with all that cash?

04:39.213 --> 04:40.312
Keep the change.

04:40.314 --> 04:42.214
Uh, to pay for stuff.

04:42.216 --> 04:43.415
Like your kid's ransom?

04:43.417 --> 04:45.217
Seems a little irresponsible,
driggity.

04:45.219 --> 04:47.486
But my knot
makes me feel more ballin'.

04:47.488 --> 04:48.553
It is quite ballin', boss.

04:48.555 --> 04:50.389
Oh.
[ Chuckling ] Oh, yeah.

04:50.391 --> 04:51.890
Do you think Jay z walks around

04:51.892 --> 04:53.558
with a big old wad of cash
in his pocket?

04:53.560 --> 04:54.326
Both: Absolutely.

04:54.328 --> 04:55.794
He does not.

04:55.796 --> 04:58.330
You really need to be putting
your money in the bank, Dre.

04:58.332 --> 04:59.431
I have money in the bank.

04:59.433 --> 05:00.999
Oh, good.
And stocks, right?

05:01.001 --> 05:03.101
And some stocks,
uh-huh.

05:03.103 --> 05:04.836
Any investment properties? [
High-pitched voice ] Well...

05:04.838 --> 05:06.672
Why is your voice getting higher?
Is it?

05:06.674 --> 05:10.175
Look, it's all about optimal
asset allocation... basic stuff.

05:10.177 --> 05:13.679
10% emerging markets, 20%
hedge funds, 30% private equity.

05:13.681 --> 05:14.846
Mm-hmm.

05:14.848 --> 05:16.415
What does your money guy
tell you

05:16.417 --> 05:17.949
about charitable donations, Dre?

05:17.951 --> 05:20.519
Let's talk charitable donations.
Mm-hmm.

05:20.521 --> 05:22.788
Go to taco bell
15 minutes before they close.

05:22.790 --> 05:25.190
They have to clean that place
out of the hard-shell items.

05:25.192 --> 05:26.658
That's the law.

05:26.660 --> 05:29.027
So, you got tacos, you
got tostadas, you got taquitos,

05:29.029 --> 05:31.430
nachos,
you've got nacho supreme.

05:31.432 --> 05:32.964
My favorite.
Mm-hmm.

05:32.966 --> 05:36.034
Point is, all that... well,
that's gonna offset your cars.

05:36.036 --> 05:37.803
Um...

05:37.805 --> 05:39.671
Dre, you're playing
in the big leagues now.

05:39.673 --> 05:41.039
So, just to be safe,

05:41.041 --> 05:43.208
why not sit down and chat
with<i> my</i> money guy?

05:43.210 --> 05:44.209
He's amazing.

05:44.211 --> 05:45.711
Uh, in the meantime,

05:45.713 --> 05:47.646
do you mind if I have another
look at that wad of cash?

05:47.648 --> 05:49.181
It's been a while

05:49.183 --> 05:51.049
since I've actually held
real currency in my hand.

05:51.051 --> 05:51.850
Hold one.

05:51.852 --> 05:53.452
Oh.

05:53.454 --> 05:55.120
Funny.

05:55.122 --> 05:59.024
This is made from the exact same
material as a cocaine straw.

06:00.494 --> 06:03.161
<i>Even though
I still felt pretty good</i>

06:03.163 --> 06:04.963
<i>about where I was financially,</i>

06:04.965 --> 06:07.899
<i>I decided it couldn't hurt
to see Stevens' guy.</i>

06:07.901 --> 06:09.801
Well, from the looks of this,
I have to say,

06:09.803 --> 06:11.903
you guys are doing great.

06:11.905 --> 06:12.971
[ Gasps ]
Oh, thank god!

06:12.973 --> 06:14.539
I told you, I got this.
Thank god.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.375
You're two professionals,
earning good salaries,

06:16.377 --> 06:17.843
homeowners with great credit.

06:17.845 --> 06:20.312
819!

06:20.314 --> 06:22.414
[ Barking ]
I pay my bills!

06:22.416 --> 06:23.548
Okay, don't do the barking.

06:23.550 --> 06:25.016
Okay.
And if you keep this up,

06:25.018 --> 06:27.138
you will be in great shape
if you decide to have kids.

06:29.523 --> 06:30.989
Uh...

06:30.991 --> 06:34.693
Yeah, uh, w-we... we...
We already have four children.

06:34.695 --> 06:36.261
Oh.
Uh-huh.

06:37.698 --> 06:38.563
You're screwed.

06:38.565 --> 06:40.232
What?
Uh...

06:40.234 --> 06:41.566
I suggest
the two of you sit down

06:41.568 --> 06:43.568
and have a very serious
discussion about money.

06:43.570 --> 06:45.370
Oh, oh, geez.

06:45.372 --> 06:46.671
8-8-819.

06:50.344 --> 06:52.077
Oh, god.

06:52.079 --> 06:54.346
How did James brown
not see this coming?

06:54.348 --> 06:56.915
Hey! Papa got a brand-new order
of onion rings!

06:56.917 --> 06:58.683
Set them right there
on that fax machine, baby.

06:58.685 --> 07:00.719
Stop talking about James brown.

07:00.721 --> 07:03.555
You said you had this handled,
and then we find out

07:03.557 --> 07:05.223
we can't send
all four of our kids to college!

07:05.225 --> 07:06.758
Jack was never going to college.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.293
I know that,

07:08.295 --> 07:11.029
but we're supposed
to be able to<i> afford</i>

07:11.031 --> 07:12.764
to send him to the college
that he can't get into.

07:12.766 --> 07:14.199
You blew it, Dre.

07:14.201 --> 07:15.233
Pops:
Sounds like money trouble.

07:15.235 --> 07:17.769
And no wonder,
the way you two spend.

07:17.771 --> 07:18.970
The latest jeans,

07:18.972 --> 07:21.940
mail-order high-top
sneaker-boot tennis shoes.

07:21.942 --> 07:23.475
When I was coming up,
all you needed was a pair

07:23.477 --> 07:24.743
of black-leather pants
and a denim vest.

07:24.745 --> 07:25.744
Didn't even need a shirt.

07:25.746 --> 07:27.312
That's why I moved to L.A.

07:27.314 --> 07:29.214
♪♪

07:29.216 --> 07:31.216
You moved to L.A.
because of that hit-and-run.

07:31.218 --> 07:32.551
This is not about me.

07:32.553 --> 07:34.619
You two are the ones trying
to keep up with the joneses.

07:34.621 --> 07:37.088
A damn sub-zero fridge.

07:37.090 --> 07:38.557
How cold does stuff
really need to be?

07:38.559 --> 07:39.958
I love my refrigerator.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.961
♪♪

07:42.963 --> 07:45.397
Pops, we work hard
for everything we have.

07:45.399 --> 07:47.432
Yes, and you're working hard
to spend it

07:47.434 --> 07:50.302
with this crazy-big house
with a guesthouse in the back.

07:50.304 --> 07:52.304
You really need to be renting
that damn thing out.

07:52.306 --> 07:53.905
You live in that guesthouse!

07:53.907 --> 07:55.307
I'm just sayin'.

07:55.309 --> 07:57.509
It's not financially
responsible.

07:57.511 --> 08:00.011
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
Oh, please.

08:00.013 --> 08:02.948
Dre, maybe we should hire
that financial planner.

08:02.950 --> 08:04.983
I don't want to lose my fridge.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.452
No! I don't trust him. What?

08:07.454 --> 08:10.255
He wasn't even impressed
with my monster credit score!

08:10.257 --> 08:13.692
Oh, my god. And it is stupid to
<i>pay</i> someone to<i> save</i> us money!

08:13.694 --> 08:14.693
I got this, bow.

08:14.695 --> 08:16.495
The only thing
that you got, Dre,

08:16.497 --> 08:18.630
is expensive sneakers
and James brown.

08:18.632 --> 08:19.998
You know what?

08:20.000 --> 08:23.435
From now on, we are gonna handle
this money thing together.

08:23.437 --> 08:24.436
Okay.

08:24.438 --> 08:26.204
<i>And</i> the kid thing, too.

08:26.206 --> 08:27.439
What?

08:27.441 --> 08:29.007
Yeah, that's right, buddy.

08:29.009 --> 08:32.511
The twins have a dentist
appointment Saturday morning.

08:32.513 --> 08:34.212
No. No.

08:37.150 --> 08:40.452
[ Sobbing ]
No, no, no, no, no!

08:40.454 --> 08:42.554
[ Sniffles ]
No, no, no, no, no, no!

08:42.556 --> 08:44.289
Hello, apple?

08:44.291 --> 08:45.490
Yeah, I'm looking
for some inside info.

08:45.492 --> 08:47.726
You know, something
that may send your stocks

08:47.728 --> 08:49.227
through the roof.

08:49.229 --> 08:51.129
Okay, well, uh, then,

08:51.131 --> 08:53.331
could you connect me to your
top-secret products division?

08:53.333 --> 08:54.699
[ Dial tone ]

08:54.701 --> 08:57.369
No insider-trading tips
over the phone?

08:57.371 --> 08:59.471
Wow. Shocking.

08:59.473 --> 09:01.973
Those apple guys are just
as tight-lipped as Nike.

09:01.975 --> 09:03.275
At least he's trying.

09:05.212 --> 09:07.913
That's just the kind of spirit
I'm looking for.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.514
Congrats.

09:09.516 --> 09:12.317
You are now the new
vice president of j&j holdings.

09:12.319 --> 09:15.053
[ Claps hands ] All right,
now, I'm looking for trends.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.222
What are you hearing?
What are you using?

09:17.224 --> 09:18.924
What are you loving?
[ Gasps ] Cookies!

09:18.926 --> 09:20.592
Delicious.
Need a better idea.

09:20.594 --> 09:22.160
Ooh!
I've got one.

09:22.162 --> 09:23.194
Quit.

09:23.196 --> 09:25.030
Not helping.
I know.

09:25.032 --> 09:27.732
I just love how you
wildly change your personality

09:27.734 --> 09:30.535
from week to week and expect
an outcome other than failure.

09:30.537 --> 09:32.604
♪♪

09:32.606 --> 09:35.206
[ Sighs ] No, I didn't get
your whatsapp.

09:35.208 --> 09:36.541
We're on wechat now.

09:36.543 --> 09:39.377
Whatsapp is old-school
and desperate...

09:39.379 --> 09:41.780
Like calling somebody, Sara.

09:41.782 --> 09:42.914
Goodbye.

09:44.551 --> 09:46.418
[ Beeping,
cash register dinging ]

09:51.024 --> 09:53.258
I think we just found
our hot-dog guy.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.427
Did we?

09:55.429 --> 09:56.494
Walk with me.

09:57.731 --> 09:59.531
[ Door closes ]

09:59.533 --> 10:02.300
How was the dentist appointment
with the twins?

10:02.302 --> 10:04.069
[ Sighing ] Oh, harrowing. Hmm.

10:04.071 --> 10:05.804
Diane may need a night guard.

10:05.806 --> 10:09.207
Jack swallowed fluoride
and has a two-week follow-up.

10:09.209 --> 10:11.610
Really hoping you can make it.

10:11.612 --> 10:13.445
So, while you were doing that,

10:13.447 --> 10:15.914
I was able to identify
our problem areas.

10:15.916 --> 10:17.482
Oh.
Mm-hmm.

10:17.484 --> 10:19.217
Mm-hmm.

10:19.219 --> 10:22.320
Sneakers, watch of the month,
unnecessary insurance.

10:22.322 --> 10:23.755
There's no such thing, bow.

10:23.757 --> 10:25.790
Tornado insurance?
You never know.

10:25.792 --> 10:27.726
Flood?
Rain happens.

10:27.728 --> 10:30.562
Volcano.
We live on a fault line!

10:30.564 --> 10:32.964
Why don't you just get us
asteroid insurance, Dre?

10:32.966 --> 10:35.233
Oh, my god.
[ Sighs ]

10:35.235 --> 10:38.303
I've left our family
totally exposed.

10:38.305 --> 10:40.305
This is ridiculous.

10:40.307 --> 10:42.407
You know what's ridiculous, bow?

10:42.409 --> 10:45.910
The things that<i> aren't</i>
on your list.

10:45.912 --> 10:47.145
Mm.

10:47.147 --> 10:49.447
Like expensive
organic hair products,

10:49.449 --> 10:53.251
weekly cuts at devachan,
crates of soy candles,

10:53.253 --> 10:56.521
fresh cut flowers,
and monthly Sage cleanses.

10:56.523 --> 10:58.523
When was the last time
any of us got possessed?

10:58.525 --> 11:01.159
Stop making my point for me.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.862
Fine, before
this gets any more hurtful,

11:03.864 --> 11:06.831
I think we should both go
on a spending diet.

11:06.833 --> 11:08.933
Mm.

